Dips Training.name: Standard Parallel Bar Dips
Dips Training.description: Grip parallel bars, lower your body, then push back up.

Dips Training.name: Bench Dips
Dips Training.description: Place your hands on a bench behind you and lower yourself.

Dips Training.name: Triceps Dips
Dips Training.description: Keep your body upright and elbows close to emphasize triceps.

Dips Training.name: Chest Dips
Dips Training.description: Lean forward slightly to target the chest more.

Dips Training.name: Explosive Dips
Dips Training.description: Push explosively at the top, optionally clapping mid-air.

Dips Training.name: Negative Dips
Dips Training.description: Lower yourself slowly to build eccentric strength.

Dips Training.name: Assisted Dips
Dips Training.description: Use a resistance band or place feet on the ground to assist the movement.

Dips Training.name: Ring Dips
Dips Training.description: Perform dips using gymnastic rings for added instability.

Dips Training.name: L-Sit Dips
Dips Training.description: Perform dips while keeping legs extended in an L position.

Dips Training.name: One-Arm Assisted Dip
Dips Training.description: Use one arm while assisting slightly with the other hand.

Dips Training.name: One-Arm Dip
Dips Training.description: Perform dips using only one arm for extreme strength training.

Dips Training.name: Korean Dips
Dips Training.description: Grip the bar behind your back and perform dips with your body in front.

Dips Training.name: Russian Dips
Dips Training.description: Lower into a dip, transition into a forearm-supported position, and push back up.

Dips Training.name: Scapular Dips
Dips Training.description: Perform small dips focusing only on scapular movement for shoulder stability.

Dips Training.name: Pike Dips
Dips Training.description: Perform dips while keeping your legs extended in a pike position.

Dips Training.name: Super Slow Dips
Dips Training.description: Perform dips with an extremely slow tempo to increase time under tension.

Dips Training.name: Floor Dips
Dips Training.description: Sit on the ground, push through your hands to lift your hips up and down.

Dips Training.name: Reverse Plank Dips
Dips Training.description: From a reverse plank, lower your body by bending your elbows and pushing back up.

Dips Training.name: Chair Dips
Dips Training.description: Perform dips using a sturdy chair as support for your hands.

Dips Training.name: Arm Swings
Dips Training.description: Swing your arms forward and backward to loosen the shoulders.

Dips Training.name: Shoulder Rolls
Dips Training.description: Roll your shoulders forward and backward in slow, controlled motions.

Dips Training.name: Wall Angels
Dips Training.description: Stand against a wall and move your arms up and down to improve shoulder mobility.

Dips Training.name: Elbow Rotations
Dips Training.description: Rotate your elbows in circular motions to warm up your joints.

Dips Training.name: Torso Twists
Dips Training.description: Gently twist your torso from side to side to activate the upper body.
